# Appointment Audit Logs & Timeline View Implementation Plan

This plan details the implementation of a comprehensive audit logging system for appointments, including a global "Audit Logs" tab for Doctors/Admins and a per-appointment "Timeline" modal.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The creation of a dedicated `AppointmentAuditLog` table will track every single state change historically. The logs will store exactly *who* (Patient, Doctor, or Admin) performed the action and *when*. 
>
> **Regarding your question about Admin actions:** Because the audit logs are tied to the Appointment, and the Appointment is tied to a specific Clinic, any action an Admin takes on a patient's appointment *will* show up in the Doctor's "Audit Logs" tab (and it will specifically indicate that the Admin performed the action).

## Open Questions
> [!WARNING]
> None at this time. The requirements are clear and the proposed solution perfectly matches industry standards for EMR audit tracking.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Backend Components

#### [NEW] `Domain\Entities\AppointmentAuditLog.cs`
- Create a new Entity to store the audit trail:
  - `LogId` (Guid, PK)
  - `AppointmentId` (Guid, FK)
  - `Action` (string - e.g., "Created", "RescheduleProposed", "Confirmed", "Cancelled", "Completed")
  - `Timestamp` (DateTime)
  - `ActorUserId` (Guid? - the user who triggered the action)
  - `ActorName` (string)
  - `ActorRole` (string - "Patient", "Doctor", "Admin")
  - `Notes` (string - optional context like reason for rejection)

#### [MODIFY] `Application\Services\AppointmentService.cs`
- Create a private helper `LogAppointmentActionAsync` that inserts rows into the new `AppointmentAuditLogs` table.
- Call this helper inside all critical state-changing methods:
  - `CreateAppointmentAsync` (Action: "Created")
  - `ApproveAppointmentAsync` & `AssignAppointmentTimeAsync` (Action: "Confirmed")
  - `ProposeRescheduleAsync` (Action: "RescheduleProposed")
  - `RespondToRescheduleAsync` (Action: "RescheduleAccepted" or "Cancelled")
  - `CancelAppointmentAsync` & `DoctorCancelAppointmentAsync` (Action: "Cancelled")
  - `CompleteAppointmentAsync` (Action: "Completed")
- Add a new query method to fetch logs: `GetAppointmentAuditLogsAsync(Guid? clinicId, Guid? appointmentId, ...)`

#### [MODIFY] `WebAPI\Controllers\AppointmentsController.cs`
- Expose `GET /api/Appointments/audit-logs` (For the global Audit Logs tab, with `clinicId` filters).
- Expose `GET /api/Appointments/{id}/audit-logs` (For the specific appointment Timeline popup).

---

### Frontend Components

#### [NEW] `src\app\features\doctor\audit-logs\audit-logs.component.*`
- Create a new standalone (or module-based) Angular component for the **Global Audit Logs**.
- **UI Details:** 
  - A Clinic Selector Dropdown ("All Clinics", "Clinic A", "Clinic B").
  - A paginated table showing: `Date/Time` | `Patient Name` | `Action Taken` | `Performed By` | `Notes`.

#### [MODIFY] `src\app\app-routing.module.ts`
- Add routing for the new Audit Logs tab:
  - `{ path: 'doctor/audit-logs', component: AuditLogsComponent }`
  - `{ path: 'admin/audit-logs', component: AuditLogsComponent }`

#### [MODIFY] `src\app\features\dashboard\dashboard.component.html` & `doctor-appointments.component.html`
- Add a `⏱️ Timeline` button next to the `📜 History` button in the action columns.
- Add a new "Activity Timeline Modal" that opens when clicked.
- This modal will call the `GET /api/Appointments/{id}/audit-logs` endpoint and render a beautiful chronological feed of everything that happened to that specific appointment.

